def: To weigh in the mind; to consider the reasons for and against;to consider maturely; to reflect upon; to ponder; as, to deliberate aquestion.
A swaying in a contrary direction; an opposing influence.[Obs.]A countersway of restraint, curbing their wild exorbitance. Milton.
Very black. [Obs.]As any raven's feathers it shone forblack. Chaucer.
Situated between or within the tropics. J. Morse.
To break completely; to break in pieces. [Obs.]With nose and mouth to-broke. Chaucer.
Formed unnaturally or illegitimately; deformed. Spenser.Milton.
